Hello new friends! Are you looking for a super sweet dog to love forever? I think you should choose me! I would make the greatest companion for a adventure, but I would also be happy right at home with you! I am great with dogs, and people too! I have lots of energy and love to give, so it would benefit me greatly to have lots of exercise. Who doesn't love a good walk with their best friend though? Take me home!

I have lots of energy and love to give, so it would benefit me greatly to have lots of exercise. Who doesn't love a good walk with their best friend though? Take me home!

Marv is a playful boy who loves all the pets in the world! Marv was a rescue we picked up, along with his brother Harry,  around the Dole Plantation. They are both so loving and can be clingy, but who doesn't love that?! Harry and Marv have been strays their whole life so it will take time to adjust to a home setting. They have settled in very nicely with us, they are pleasant on the leash and very friendly. Ask us more about the dynamic duo and adopt Marv today or both of the brothers!

This is one Lab who you can still teach new tricks! I came to Kauai Humane Society as a stray, so the staff isn't sure what my home life was like before I came here. However, they have learned that I LOVE TO LEARN - and treats motivate me to learn all sorts of tricks! I sit and give good eye contact and have learned to walk better on leash all through treats and calm, consistent training.

That's what I would like in my new home - calm, consistent training (and some treats). :-)

I can be initially slow to warm up to people and prone to escape if not handled securely; hence why that consistent training and treats is so important. ;-) And within a day or so, I will warm up and learn my routine so fast!

I have met some dogs I was a little unsure about, and other easy-going, very social puppies that I have done great with. The key to my heart, and to being my best-matched home, is understanding I might start out needing more patience and initial routine than your average pet. Watching me learn and grow is so rewarding!

Hina is as lovable a gal as they come!  She adores humans, can get rambunctious and mouthy so not a good fit for kids.  She is happy going on a couple leisurely walks a day and snoozing in between.  Hina would thrive as the only dog with humans who are savvy to the bully breeds.  She is strong, but never malicious with her exuberance.  We have had Hina in our care for several years and would love to see her find a home of her own where she is queen.  She is currently on the island of Kauai, with travel of bully breeds becoming increasingly restrictive, we understand it will be a challenge to get her to the mainland.  However, we are open to homes within the state of Hawaii.

Furikake is a fun and energetic kitten, loves to play with his sister (Nori, also available for adoption). He was born with a bent tail, but it does not bother him or prevent him from living his best life. He is outgoing and adjust to new environment quickly. His favorite toys are laser pointers, cat teaser toys and fuzzy ball. 



He is flea bathed, neutered, microchipped, vaccinated

chance was rescued from an area near Kapahulu Ave and Ekela. He was a frequent guest at an apartment complex where the security did not approve of him coming into the building. Hes nervous at first but is kind, gentle, and soft. He likes to be held and he enjoys chin skritches! This guy deserves all the best after being stuck outdoors for so long. Please fill out an application for Chance at www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt

Miss Burger and Miss McFlurry are tiny little panthers who stalk toys and protect me from invading feathers and keep the soft mice at bay by swatting them under the couch.  I owe them my undying gratitude for ensuring my safety. They are sweet lapcats and generous with their kisses.  



Miss Burger and Miss McFlurry are identical twins, I mean totally identical.  No one can tell them apart.  They are 2/3 of the Makaha Happy Meal and equally sweet and tasty.  They have sleek and silky coats and fly up the cat trees like squirrels.  But once they crash, they are down for the count.

Cloud was a mama outdoor cat who's babies were in a dangerous area. Cloud and her babies were brought in to safety and to be raised by a foster home. Cloud is a sweet and mild kitty cat. She likes to watch the room from afar and she will chatter at birds in the window. We are actively working to socialize Cloud better. Shes timid, but sweet n cuddly too! She likes dogs and other cats but does not like kids so much.

Morocco is an 8yr old sweet loving cat. He was rehomed by his original owner for about a year, but he was unfortunately neglected by them and was returned to his original owner. When he returned, he was over weight and had matted furr. He is currently on a special diet for his urinary crystals and to bring his weight down. His original owner can no longer keep him due to health issues, so we are looking for someone who is willing to give him a loving furever home.

Nikki was trapped and left in a cage x5 days with no food or water. When brought in, she had 4 little babies and surrogated 9 additional. Her mom skills are impeccable and she deserves a great new home of her own!

Ghost is a Flame Point Siamese boy, who came from a homeless camp where he was cared for by a woman who wanted him to have a happy, easy life. He is a charming lap cat with a calm disposition and a very impressive purr! Ghost will only be adopted as a pair with one of his siblings, Pumpkin or Tricks.

Macaroni!!!! He had an accessed back and couldn't walk well! Rescued by members of Catopia Hawaii, then we fostered him back to health! Macaroni is his name because his back had a bend like a macaroni noodle. Macaroni loves to observe. Hes often scared of new surroundings, but adjusts in due time. He love to seek out companionship with other kitties. Hes alsways got a look of great concern on his face, but thats just his RBF.
Pringle was abandoned by his previous family, but is looking for a new one! Sweet and cuddly, Pringle will likely snuggle with you in bed. He also loves chatting!

Dyson is a very finicky and dynamic kitty! He's got a crochetty "Mraaaooow" sound and LOVES wet food! He really likes time by himself as he observes the humans of the house. Dyson gets a kick out of laser pointing and his favorite treat is temptation or bacon bits! He likes to be pet, but not picked up much. His eyes are BRIGHT BLUE! He loves to find the warm rays of sunshine and bask in them on the floor. Someone with patience will be needed, but his warmth, love and generous petting will be so worth it!

Tricks is a dark ginger tabby boy, who was cared for from an early age by a homeless woman who wanted a better life for him. He is very sweet and cuddly, but has a high energy playful side as well. Tricks would love to be adopted with one of his siblings, Ghost or Pumpkin, or by a family who already has a kitten his age for him to play with. Maybe his next trick could be stealing your heart?
This little one is getting ready for the day he will be ready for adoption. www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt

This little nugget was found on the road of Kaneohe marine corps base by some visitors to the island. They took good care of him, took him on adventures, and called Lucky Paws to help before they depart Oahu. This kitty is a top gem. Very social already and likes dogs and cats alike thus far. has lots of energy.

Izzy is FIV/ FELV negative and parasite-free.  She is a sweet girl who is very playful and independent,  She loves playing with toys and chasing small balls.   Izzy was rescued as a small kitten and found tangled up in vines.

This little girl was found with sibling Bullseye. Both had terrible ringworm which is being treated. The ringworm makes for a terrible picture but she will be a beautiful white and orange kitty when healed.

McNugget was found living under a McDonalds Dumpster in mililani. He was just a kitten and was by himself with no colony nearby. He was adopted, but then released to the wild where he was recaptured and then turned into HHS. Because he was microchipped, we got a call to pick him up and now he is prepped for a new adventure. Hes very sweet. LOVES to be pet, but doesnt like to be held until he gets to know you. Hes playful like a kitten. He likes dogs and other cats just fine! He loves naps and pushes his nose into you every night demanding affection! Top notch kitty!

Miss Burger and Miss McFlurry are identical twins, I mean totally identical.  No one can tell them apart.  They are 2/3 of the Makaha Happy Meal and equally sweet and tasty.  They have sleek and silky coats and fly up the cat trees like squirrels.  But once they crash, they are down for the count.

Izzy is a little over 3 month old and is playful, independent and a loving cat that also has a feisty side.  She was rescued, she was tangled up in weeds. A good samaritan was able to get her out of it.  She does well with other cats with a slow introduction, but she don't not mind getting all the attention to herself. She loves being pet and playing with fuzzy ball. She would do best in a household without any children.

This was part of a litter who was rescued from Sonny's Auto at Sand Island. Mama was missing and babies were in a bad place. Flashy is FAST! She loves to play and dart around the cage. She enjoys wrestling the siblings, eating slurry, and taking long naps. Very cuddly and loves to sleep near your head. She is just a little kitty but shes a BIG treasure! Shes VERY cottonball-like and is calico. Mostly Grey, legs white, orange stripe on face. Very cool!
Very friendly and perky kitty! She loves to cuddle and be pet and also to play! Ziggy was named after her ziggy zag shaped tail tip.

Bellatrix (Bella) is a beautiful Siamese kitty who was rescued from the Ranch 99 in Moanalua after a security guard witnessed her be dumped out of a van by her former owner. She recently had three babies, but will be spayed and ready to go to her forever home in mid October when she is done nursing. Bella is extremely affectionate and loves to be around people, especially calm children. She isn't shy about letting you know when she wants pets! She would do well being adopted with her kitten (Ginny), or as an only cat, or possibly into a home with other cats after a proper slow introduction. She is an excellent mother who deserves to be spoiled by her very own forever family after she's done raising her kittens.

Princess is a dynamic kitty! She loves the head to tail petting! She has the cutest meows and arches up her back when you touch her. She likes to attack anything that has strings or tassels and is playful. She absolutely goes nuts for shredded chicken and tuna juice is her jam! Dontcha just love her fluffy white chest?! Shes very bonded with her sister, Princess.
Baby was found in Kapolei next to the deceased mother. Saved by a locksmith and surrendered to Lucky Paws. Adopt at www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt

Pumpkin is a light ginger little girl, who has been very loved by humans from the beginning of her life. She was cared for by a homeless woman who realized she could not provide the life she wanted this sweet girl to have. Pumpkin's motto is play hard, nap harder. If you sit down around her, be prepared for her to climb into your lap immediately, it's her favorite place to be! Pumpkin would like to be adopted with one of her brothers, Tricks or Ghost, or by a family who already has a young kitty for her to play with.

General Pebbles is highly curious and adventuresome. He is mechanically minded and studies all the new toys and marvels at the workings of water fountains with avid interest and concentration. He is an affectionate lap cat and generous with his kisses.

Boris the Blade is a battle hardened street cat who got socialized by humans and is now living the good life! An A-1 nap-master deserves a an absolutely chill environment where he can lounge and be spoiled. He's had all of his teeth removed so he drools a bit.. which we find endearing. Loves kittens, loves wet food. Slightly hard of hearing, and slightly hard of seeing but really enjoys staying indoors and finding the softest spot in the house.

Goose is about 5 month old as of 8/31/21. He can be a little skittish at first, but once he opens up, he is playful, energetic and cuddly. 

He is vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, Fiv/Felv negative, dewormed, littler trained and flea bathed.

Hi, I'm Loki. I was about to be dumped in a park in San Francisco when a Good Samaritan saw what was happening and intervened. My rescuer talked to the person dumping me and persuaded them to hand me over instead of abandoning me. From there I made my way to SaveABunny.



It was clear I was neglected as I was very skinny and had an old injury -- what looks like a broken leg that was never attended to so it healed a bit crooked, but it doesn't bother me so the vet says just to monitor. I can't tell you how happy I am to be safe and cared for -- and I'm a girl ready to let bygones be bygones and look forward to finding a forever home.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

I want a partner who lives in the slow-lane -- someone who sits a lot and enjoys having a warm, soft bunny lounging side-by-side. In our Bunny Zen zone we can: post photos of the two of us snuggling and make everyone jealous; sing our favorite tunes; watch silly videos of bunnies snuggling; stare out the window and blissfully mind-wander; share our forever love. I'm shy and would appreciate a quiet companion who will help me become all I am capable of becoming. P.S. Are salads on the menu twice a day? I'll come happily hopping. Not shy about that!
